Text.Value: Please, she was weak. Your kind don't avenge those who fail.
You are quite remarkable.
I can promise you fewer secrets?
Speaking out of turn is an indiscretion. Trying to drink my blood is something else entirely.

EditorData.logicalname: ASTARION BIT SH AND FAILED PERSUADE

Text.Value: Don't worry, from now on I'll focus on our enemies.
Don't treat me like an idiot, please. I have a talent for recognising when someone has a secret.
Secrets keep me safe. You'll just have to live with that.
I don't doubt that, funnily enough.
Perhaps we can... come to an arrangement.
A vamp, huh? Interesting. Keep your teeth to yourself, Astarion, and we won't have any issues.
There's more to this, I'm sure of it.
A little ironic, no? I have a feeling you have a few secrets of your own. More than a few, in fact.
I tried. Enjoy your new status as pariah.
I shall. Nightly.
I mean... never mind. Let's consider the matter settled.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight stammer on unintended innuendo.

Text.Value: The distinction's lost on me, if you still feed on blood.
I see... and what gave me away?
I let you keep your head. But that doesn't mean you have my trust.
Anyway, you'd burn your tongue off if you went for this neck.
So you're a vampire, Astarion? I suppose I shouldn't really act surprised - the signs are not exactly subtle, if you care to look.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character saw Astarion use his 'bite' ability on someone else (probably in combat, but not necessarily) and confronts him about being a vampire.
EditorData.NodeContext: Confrontational. Just learned Astarion is a vampire after he bit someone

Text.Value: *A dreadful idea. Shadowheart hasn't exactly warmed to you so far - she's bound to take the revelation badly.*
But I trust we can all sleep a little more soundly in camp now - well, apart from you, of course.
But I trust we can all sleep a little more soundly in camp now.
I'll take it on good faith that such a thing exists.

EditorData.NodeContext: Teasing/not intended to sound too harsh.

Text.Value: First you exhibit strange magic, now Lae'zel explodes. That sounds like a link to me.
Lae'zel might be a reluctant ally, but she is good at killing. I'll point her in their direction.
So you're not in full control of your faculties. If you think it might happen again, warn me. I would hate to have to kill you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cautious

Text.Value: Change your mind. The secret can keep for now.
That's good. I'd rather keep things friendly between all of us.

Whatever you think may be compelling you... you may have greater ability to resist it than you realise. Everyone has unseemly thoughts. Being able to quieten them is what sets us apart from the beasts.
For his sake, he best not develop an appetite for githyanki.
Although... perhaps it won't.
Fine. But don't take me for granted - not my company, and certainly not my blood.

EditorData.NodeContext: Ultimatum. Willing to let it go if Astarion behaves.

Text.Value: No loss to our little venture, either way.
I suppose I can understand that. More than most, perhaps.
Best if you leave me alone, for now.
Gods-damned leech - you bit me!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character was bitten by Astarion in gameplay.
EditorData.NodeContext: Outraged. Astarion just bit her.
EditorData.logicalname: WAS BITTEN BY AST IN GAMEPLAY

Text.Value: I don't want to discuss it.
What happened was my dagger finding the back of her throat.
I understand why you ask but memory loss is not as uncommon as you'd think. There may be other causes.
I should have known you were a vampire - the signs were there.

EditorData.NodeContext: Outraged. Astarion just bit her.

Text.Value: Concerned about turning into a monster? You're already halfway there, by most standards.
Understood.
And yet, it seems the one who gave those orders has run afoul of my goddess. Delivering the artefact is no longer my mission - cleansing Lady Shar's church is my mission.
Somehow, I'm not sure I'll take your word for it just yet. A little more trust needs to be cultivated first.
Perhaps I'm a better liar than you are, then. All the more reason to be honest with me - I'll see right through you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Poker face. Veiled reference to the fact her shar worship is a secret at present

Text.Value: Confess the truth to her.
I've seen your resolve. Whatever is trying to control you, you're stronger.

EditorData.NodeContext: Supportive

Text.Value: We still have use for each other. But perhaps one day, that will no longer be the case.
Of course it is, and I said nothing about friendship. But a little less tension between us might benefit all.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to be reasonable/diplomatic after a near-fatal blowout with Lae'zel

Text.Value: My kin don't just explode.
People don't just explode. I assume that's true of gith too.
*Is this a good idea, you wonder? You and Shadowheart have a certain rapport, but is it strong enough to weather such a revelation?*
I suppose that makes you quite remarkable... though not in a way I'd envy, perhaps.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wary

Text.Value: We could always spar if you want to practise.
I'd just better not wake in the night to find fangs at my throat.
Your stealth was commendable. Your flaw was to talk rather than strike.
I'd advise against satisfying your hunger on me. Who knows what the orb might do if it realises its host is the one being drained.
I won't regret defending myself. There's nothing more to it.
You're a bad liar. And perhaps an untrustworthy ally.
Are you looking for the lurid details?
How kind of you to remind me. But I don't think so - you've a tadpole too and seem stronger than ever.
I'm surprised you didn't leave.
Very well - but I'm keeping an eye on you. And no wisecracks about having us for supper.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said to Astarion directly

Text.Value: I will respect our truce, if you do the same.
Rubbish! Your senses have taken leave of you, Shadowheart.
I hope you can keep your cravings in check, going forward. Otherwise, I think you and I will be parting ways - understood?
Well, let's hope he keeps his distance.
Coming from you, I'll take that as a victory.

EditorData.NodeContext: Teasing/not intended to sound too harsh.

Text.Value: I'll just have to try get some more rest when we next stop to camp...
Don't waste your time deciphering the actions of a lunatic.
I sincerely hope you're worth the trouble.
You speak with all the sincerity of a vulture pecking at carrion.
She went mad, now she's dead. What's there to talk about?
I confronted you in Vlaakith's name. Our conflict serves no purpose now.
You have my sympathies - especially after what Shar did to me. Perhaps you and I met the same ill fortune in who we came to serve.
Well, the truth's out now, in either case. Did you want something else?
Don't treat me like an idiot, please. Do you think it was easy for me, to try keeping my faith hidden? I know when someone's burdened with a secret.
So we're travelling with a vampire, are we?
And you've been keeping this from me all this time...? I thought we trusted one another.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little hurt. Astarion, who she has a good relationship with up until, confessed he's a vampire. This reaction is due to a failed skillcheck - she can also react more positively elsewhere.

Text.Value: But there are bigger, more immediate concerns. Let's put survival first, for now.
You took the words right out of my mouth.
I'm surprised I managed to get some rest, after last night's interruption.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Avatar Astarion tried to bite this companion during the night, but you woke up and discovered he was a vampire. You talked it through and resolved things peacefully in CAMP_AstarionHunger_IVB_SCO_Avatar_Choice.lsj
EditorData.NodeContext: Lingering sore feelings/suspicion. Caught avatar Astarion trying to drink her blood the night before, but he made amends.

Why didn't you tell me?
I'll be watching you closely.
Admit the truth to her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Self-awarness/outreach (referring to her outed secret about being a shar worshipper)

Text.Value: I lost more than a few comrades to your kin, but we were infiltrating githyanki territory. Blood was spilled on both sides - just soldiers following orders.

I haven't stabbed you.
Lady Shar willed it to fall... though even I won't quite revel in all those deaths as much as you. The unfaithful were vanquished, but I have little interest in slavering over their corpses.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some distaste

EditorData.NodeContext: Cold

Text.Value: I'd advise against satisfying your hunger on me. Who knows what the orb might do if it realises its host is the one being drained.

EditorData.NodeContext: Ultimatum. Willing to let it go if Astarion behaves.

Text.Value: Hells. Why can't I just have normal, boring companions? I should be grateful you told me, at least.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Just my luck'/some exasperation. Astarion just confessed he's a vampire.

Text.Value: Yeah. And I'm way too hot to touch.

Good. I knew you had what it took to quieten your demons. I'd hate to have lost the real you.
*You and Shadowheart have forged a strong bond. Surely she will understand...*
Having one less enemy to worry about mightn't count for much - not with the odds we're facing... but having more than that - an ally to count on, or even a, well...

EditorData.NodeContext: Tough. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I'll be keeping an eye on both of you. I don't want a fight happening again.
But should I wake with so much as a drop of blood on my neck, I will end him.
I'm not entirely without sympathy, I should say. To fall out with someone you revered... it must be catastrophic.
A vampire could make for an interesting ally in combat, if nothing else.
Are you all right? You were wounded.
Pray that you never find yourself in the same position.
You have a faraway look on your face, Astarion. Did you forget what you were going to say? Happens to the best of us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight bemusement (avatar astarion considered confessing he is a vampire, only change his  mind  and say nothing)

Peckish...?!

EditorData.NodeContext: Dumbstruck

Text.Value: Lady Shar is patient though - she can wait until the rest of you have torn each other apart.
It's no great mystery - I just wasn't sure if I could trust you.
I promise, I'll do my best to resist my hunger.
So... a vampire spawn. Is my throat safe?
There's nothing more for you to uncover here. Let it rest.

You know... I had my suspicions, but I didn't want to act on them. And now it seems I won't have to.
Fine - as long as he keeps his fangs off our necks.
Yet.
We aren't dear friends now, if that's what you're asking.
Let's not dance around the subject - I know you're a vampire.
So we're travelling with a vampire, are we? Of course we are.
Yet I no longer follow those orders. Shar has abandoned me. The artefact is no longer my mission - saving my family is.
When we make it to Baldur's Gate, you'll be at home in the slaughterhouses.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some distaste

Text.Value: I'd be lying if I said I hadn't noticed the spasms and the fainting spells. You have my commiserations - I think I know how it must feel, in a sense.
You, of all people, cannot criticise me on the subject of keeping secrets.
True. Your proclivities might not matter at all soon enough, if we don't find a cure.
You know... I had my suspicions, but I didn't want to act on them. And now it seems I won't have to.
So you're a vampire, Astarion? I suppose I shouldn't really act surprised - the signs are not exactly subtle, if you care to look.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quietly aghast

Text.Value: But no more secrets, understand?
The truth's out now, no thanks to you. No more secrets, understand?
Our enmity is a festering wound - it weakens us both. It must be sucked clean.
I have more important things to worry about than your throat - the tadpole, for one.
It was always an uneasy pairing. I'm going to just trust that you had your reasons.
We're all in this together. Provided you can keep your urges in check around me, I don't see why anything has to change.
A word of warning, Astarion: I taste absolutely awful.
You're the last thing the world needs - another would-be tyrant who thinks they have divine rights. You're just someone's pawn, you know. That's all we are to the gods.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tough. Arc: Shadowheart has rejected Shar

Text.Value: Interesting.
Well the truth's out now, for what it's worth. Are we done?

Thank you for the advice. See? We have much to learn from each other.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry

Text.Value: I see. It must be difficult, have someone you revere turn on you. I'm willing to let the past go, if you are as well.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tiny hint of understanding between frenemies.

Text.Value: I knew there was something untrustworthy about you.
Don't try it again. If you feel the urge, go find yourself a sheep or something.
Tell her the truth.
So, your very own queen has turned on you...? Your people are nothing if not ruthless.
Don't give it a second thought. I'll persevere.
Now that we have some semblance of an understanding, did you want anything else?
You're hardly alone - bloodletting is quite popular of late. Though your twinge of conscience sets you apart from the brigands, monsters and kill-happy fiends of the world...
Only a glancing blow. Clearly you gith aren't quite the killers they believe themselves to be.
Only a glancing blow. Clearly gith aren't quite the killers they believe themselves to be.
I'll try poison next time. That was a joke, just to be clear.
You do that. I'll do something more productive, like find a cure.
Besides, just look at yourself. It couldn't be any more obvious.
No, I don't think so - you've a tadpole as well but you see fine...
Vamps don't scare me. As long as they keep their teeth to themselves.
Relax. We'll kiss and make up on our own time.
And people don't just hear each other's thoughts, or turn into monsters. And yet...
From me, at least. But if my old master comes knocking, all bets are off.
Would you have had the self-control to not drain me dry if I hadn't stirred? I'm not sure I want to think about it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Lingering sore feelings/suspicion. Caught avatar Astarion trying to drink her blood the night before, but he made amends.

Text.Value: Hunting with vampires? Never thought I'd see the day.
My master forbid me from revealing my true nature.
I appreciate it, but keep your guard up around others. We're gathering enemies by the day.
Don't sound so disappointed.
Calm down - I'm on your side. I just got a little... peckish.
A word of warning, Astarion: I taste absolutely awful. Keep your distance.
No, I think you'd stab me from the front, if it came to that.
No more secrets, on my honour.
Your queen turned on you, and my goddess turned on me. Perhaps we have more in common than we dare admit to.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tiny hint of understanding between frenemies.

Text.Value: No sense judging someone for who they are. Except devils, obviously.
Perhaps I should have said something before you actually bit someone.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confrontational. Just learned Astarion is a vampire after he bit someone

Text.Value: Let me see - the deathly-pale skin? The red eyes? The fangs? I'm not blind, you know.
You want to be friends? What a foolish notion.
It isn't. Now let's leave it at that.
Thank you for your clumsy platitudes and maudlin sympathies.
You think I wouldn't have understood? We've all got a bigger problem to contend with - we need to be able to rely on one another.
And by that, I mean, never bring up the subject again.
Safe as houses.
Very well. At least you are consistent.

EditorData.NodeContext: Brusque

Text.Value: Technically I'm a vampire spawn.
I never claimed to be wise, unfortunately.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unintimidated

Text.Value: Then I won't breathe another word about it. But the sentiment remains the same. Chin up.
That's good enough for me.
I've made enough enemies. I'd welcome a kinship.
A vampire among us? So be it.
Plumbing for guilt is pointless. I did what I must.
Lady Shar chose me also, but because of the blood I spilled, not what flows in my veins. You are born of murder itself... perhaps your fate is out of your hands.
Careful. I'm not sure I can withstand the charm.
If you say so. Our last discussion grew... heated. I'd rather not repeat it.
An arrangement? Explain.
Well, at least I know I won't find you atop me in the middle of the night now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitant, but genuine

Synopsis: Default dialogue - the conversation you can have with Shadowheart at any time when she's a member of your party. You can ask her about herself, or events that you've experienced together during your adventures. Her responses to you may differ slightly depending on her current attitude towards you.
